The Backstreet Boys' song "Everybody (Backstreet's Back)" isÂ a party anthem that conveys a sense of fun and celebration.Â The song's title and chorus are enough to get the message across, with the rest of the song reinforcing it.Â  ExplanationÂ  The song's synth lines change pitch, helping the listener follow the song's trajectory. The verses are short and to the point, as the song doesn't have a complex story. The song's title and chorus convey the song's message. Music video The music video for "Everybody (Backstreet's Back)" was inspired by Michael Jackson's "Thriller" and featured a haunted house aesthetic.Â  The video showed the band members spending the night in a creepy mansion after their tour bus broke down.Â  The video director matched each band member's personality with a character in the video.
